entry.summary:
I'm maintaining a project built with Tailwind at work. I'm no daily Tailwinder, but usually, I manage just fine. But recently, a trivial task took me quite some time to get right. I wanted to rotate an SVG icon depending on the details element's :open state.
Getting started with Tailwind is straightforward (a CSS property just maps to a class name, right?), but I still have to wrap my head around advanced features like class-based element relationships.
How would you achieve the following CSS in Tailwind?
details:open svg {
  rotate: 0.5turn;
}

